.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-PEERS-SCORE" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-peers-score \- rank peers by channel health score
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-peers-score
.SH DESCRIPTION
Scores all peers by a weighted channel health metric and returns them
sorted descending by score (0\(en100).
.PP
Scoring components:
.TP 4
40 pts
Balance score — peaks at 50% local ratio; lower when a channel is
fully drained toward either side.
.TP 4
20 pts
Connectivity — peer is currently connected.
.TP 4
20 pts
Channel count — full score for 2 or more channels, partial for 1.
.PP
Output format (JSON array):
.nf
[{peer_id, alias, score, num_channels,
  local_sat, remote_sat, connected, local_ratio}]
.fi
.PP
Returns an empty array when the daemon is not reachable.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-health (1),
.BR lightning-peer-list (1),
.BR lightning-channel-list (1)
